column4:
Worker date of birth
(Must be in the format of dd/mm/yyyy, must be today or in the past but less than 130 years ago.)
column6:
Worker National Insurance number
(There must be an entry if there is no passport number or national identity card number. Format must be 2 letters then 6 digits then A, B, C, D or a space, like QQ123456C or QQ123456 .)
column12:
Worker engagement details
(Select how the worker was engaged to provide their services.

� A: Self-employed contractor
� B: Partnership
� C: Limited liability partnership
� D: Limited company
� E: Another party operated PAYE on the worker's payments)
column13:
Worker unique taxpayer reference (UTR)
(There must be an entry if 'Worker engagement details' is 'A', 'B' or 'C'. Entry must be 10 numbers.)
column14:
Start date of engagement
(Must be in the format of dd/mm/yyyy, must be today or in the past and may be before the start of the reporting period if the engagement has never ended.)
column15:
End date of engagement 
(Must be an entry if the engagement has ended, entry must be in the format of dd/mm/yyyy and must be the same as or after the start date, today or in the past, and in the reporting period the report relates to.)
column16:
Amount paid for the worker's services
(Numeric value to 2 decimal places, you should round to the nearest penny.)
column18:
Is this amount inclusive of VAT?
(Y or N)

column21:

(Maximum 35 characters)
column22:

column23:
Address line 4 of party paid by intermediary for worker's services
